laboratory_examinations.findings: Interval increase in the number of heterogeneous microcalcifications, classified as BI-RADS category 5 (highly suggestive of malignancy).
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Abnormal mammogram in 2008 with microcalcifications (BI-RADS category 3), followed by increased findings in 2010.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Identified ductal carcinoma in situ (DCIS), intermediate grade without comedo-type necrosis, on 2 of 9 slides. Estrogen receptor staining was strongly positive.
